# Trivy IaC/misconfig ignore list — EPIC-14 #89 baseline triage.
#
# Read before adding an entry: this file makes `trivy-config` in
# .github/workflows/security-scan.yml BLOCKING (exit-code 1, #89). Every entry
# below is a specific, already-triaged finding with a stated reason it's an
# accepted risk or a false positive — not a blanket suppression. New findings
# introduced by future changes are NOT covered by anything here and will fail
# CI as intended; add a new dated, justified entry only after the same triage
# rigor, or fix the underlying misconfig instead.

# KSV-0109 (ConfigMap with secrets) — infra/helm/beekeepingit/charts/authentik/
# templates/blueprint-configmap.yaml, flagging the Authentik declarative
# blueprint's seed-user `password: dev-password123`
# (infra/helm/beekeepingit/charts/authentik/files/beekeepingit.blueprint.yaml).
# Accepted: this is a fixed, non-secret dev/CI login for the
# `test.beekeeper@beekeepingit.local` seed account used only by the local k3d
# dev cluster and the ephemeral CI k3d job (helm-e2e.yml) — both
# world-disposable environments with no real user data, torn down after every
# run. It grants no access to anything outside that ephemeral cluster. Moving
# it to a generated Secret would need the blueprint's YAML templating to
# reference a Secret key (Authentik blueprints don't support that natively —
# only ConfigMap-delivered file content), a nontrivial rework out of scope for
# this triage pass. Production-grade IdP hardening (real accounts, no seed
# user) is explicitly deferred to EPIC-14 (docs/architecture/platform.md "Not
# yet covered here").
KSV-0109

# KSV-0014 (root filesystem not read-only) + KSV-0118 (default security
# context) — currently only fires on
# infra/helm/beekeepingit/charts/powersync/templates/deployment.yaml.
# Deferred, not accepted-forever: `journeyapps/powersync-service` is a
# third-party image with no in-repo Dockerfile to inspect. This PR cannot run
# a live cluster (#89's constraint) to verify its runtime user or whether it
# writes to its own root filesystem (e.g. Node/npm caches) — setting
# `runAsNonRoot`/`readOnlyRootFilesystem` unverified risks a silent
# crash-loop that only a real deploy would catch. The container-level
# hardening that IS safe regardless of the image's internals
# (allowPrivilegeEscalation: false, capabilities drop ALL) is already applied
# — see that file. Every OTHER Deployment in the umbrella chart
# (pwa/services/*) already sets a full securityContext (readOnlyRootFilesystem
# included) as of this same PR, so this ignore is not currently masking
# anything else.
#
# CAVEAT (trivy's .trivyignore has no per-resource scoping for misconfig
# checks — a bare check ID is ignored repo-wide): until this entry is
# resolved, a FUTURE Deployment added without its own securityContext would
# also be silently ignored by these two IDs rather than caught by CI. Kept
# narrow at review time by convention (new charts should copy the
# pwa/services pattern), tracked to close on issue #89 — validate
# PowerSync's image against a live rollout, apply the two settings there, and
# delete this whole entry (restoring full KSV-0014/KSV-0118 coverage).
KSV-0014
KSV-0118
